latestIgtvVideos.title: How to get a slim/toned face without using any face tools
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
No botox, No face tools 💆These 5 massages using ur hands n knuckles will chisel your face.👐

Apply any facial oil after Moisturizing.🧴

👉Upward motion with knuckles for lifted cheekbones. Repeat this 20 times. 

👉For prefect jawline use your knuckles and lift it with slight pressure upwards. Repeat 30 times

👉For droopy eyebrows 👁️ use your fingers and pull each eyebrow upwards 100 times. 

👉Using hands in upward massage motion get rid of that double chin. Repeat this 50 times. 

👉Since the under eye area is very delicate. Use slightest pressure with knuckles and lift upwards. Repeat 20 times
.
Disclaimer- I’m not a Yoga expert but after extensive research I started these massages and it helped me achieve desired results. And no kind of exercises can ever bring 100% results untill you  follow a healthy clean eating lifestyle along. All the best 🥰

#unsponsored Skincare has truly been a journey for me, and I’m so excited to share these personal lessons with all of you. But before that pls hit the 🚩FOLLOW button.
*Treatment routine is pinned in comments

✨SPF –I seriously stepped up my sunscreen game. I used to be inconsistent, and it showed pigmentation,dullness, and dehydrated skin. Now, SPF is non-negotiable for me.
✨VITAMIN C – It took me a while to trust that Vitamin C actually works. But after finding the right formula for my skin and using it consistently, I saw a transformation.
✨RETINOL- I almost gave up using retinols before,because of the initial purging and dullness. But once I understood how it works, I stuck with it and now use it 2–3 times a week. 
✨SKIN BARRIER MOISTURISER – this one is underrated but crucial part of skincare Its protecting your skin barrier. A strong barrier keeps your skin healthy, glowing, and less reactive. Moisturiser isn’t just about hydration,it seals in all the layers you’ve applied and helps repair and maintain your barrier. Never skip it, even if your skin feels oily!
✨RICE TONER– I added a rice toner to my morning routine and wow, the glow is unreal! I’ve made so many videos about it because it’s truly that good.
✨TREATMENT– I use salicylic acid, glycolic, or lactic acid serums and niacinamide serum While they make the skin clear n brighter , overuse may damage ur skin barrier.
✨FACE MASSAGE – I’ve talked about this before-lymphatic drainage and increased blood circulation have helped my skin immensely, especially with puffiness and dark circles.
✨COLLAGEN – I don’t apply collagen topically . I recently started taking  supplements instead. 
✨EYE CREAM – ITS A MUST! It will smooth fine lines and brighten under-eyes with regular use.
✨PATIENCE – Please stop stressing over trends or hoping for a miracle product. There’s no magic serum! It takes time, discipline, and consistency. For me, it’s been a 5-year process.

Disclaimer- Lifestyle changes and eating habits added along also make a huge difference on skin

Comment ‘LINK’ if you’d like me to DM u some product recommendations 

Ps do a patch test before using.

Keep glowing and stay consistent!
